sql:
SELECT p.package_name, p.description, p.version, p.license
FROM packages p
JOIN heaviness h ON p.package_id = h.package_id
WHERE p.status = 'active' AND h.heaviness_score > (
    SELECT AVG(heaviness_score) FROM heaviness
);

SELECT package_id, AVG(average_usage_time)
FROM package_usage_stats
GROUP BY package_id;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM package_versions
WHERE is_stable = 0;

external_knowledge:
- Active packages: Packages with a status of 'active'.;
- Frequently used: Packages with a usage count greater than one.;
- Impact on resources: Heaviness score indicating the resource impact.;
- Stability ratings: Stability score based on the RISCA framework.
